text: Turtle Bay is a neighborhood in the Manhattan Borough of New York state. It is most recognized for constituting the United Nations Headquarters, Chrysler Building, St Bartholomew's Church and the Grand Central Station at its south boundary. Turtle Bay is on the far east side of Midtown Manhattan starting at 5th Avenue and onwards, and between E 42nd and E 59th street vertically. Category:Neighborhoods of New York City Category:Manhattan
title: Turtle Bay, Manhattan
